title: Spain suspends Catalonia independence vote
description:
Spain's constitutional court has suspended a planned referendum on independence by the Catalonia region.   Judges say they need to decide whether the 9 November vote will be a breach of spanish law. Energised by Scotland's recent independence referendum, the Catalan government insists it will push ahead with the vote. Al Jazeera's Jonah Hull reports from Barcelona.
